OL,6, The overhead projector, for example. A 
OL,7, rugged bit of kit, built for one job.  
OL,8, Take this see-through sheet of plastic 
OL,9, and splatter the beige wall with its   
OL,10, contents. Simple enough. A lightbulb,  
OL,11, a couple of lenses, a mirror, and a big
OL,12, steel box and, come to think of it, a  
OL,13, bit of steel box for the arm.          
OL,15, Ok, so it had some glass in it, that's 
OL,16, not 100% foolproof. But it was robust  
OL,17, and lacked the irreparable complexity  
OL,18, of a modern projector. When's the last 
OL,19, time you saw someone actually use one  
OL,20, of those "smartboards" properly anyway?
