OL,6, Maybe that was a bad example. How about
OL,7, the BBC Micro? Computer for the ages.  
OL,8, Well, ages 5 to 16 or so, at least in  
OL,9, the 80s.                               
OL,11, Anyway, a big lump of a computer, maybe
OL,12, not by PC standards, but its peers were
OL,13, often more svelte. Take the ZX Spectrum
OL,14, with its diminutive keyboard that was  
OL,15, like... ok, no, sorry, I'm being trite,
OL,16, everybody's insulted the poor thing's  
OL,17, keyboard by now. Anyway, the rugged and
OL,18, portly Beeb was built to withstand the 
OL,19, ever-present threat of two dozen kids  
OL,20, with all the finesse of a jackhammer.  
